  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the mean length of hospital stay in laparoscopic trans abdominal preperitoneal&#xD;
      repair versus open mesh repair in patients undergoing inguinal hernia repair with mesh.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A total of 334 patients of male gender with Inguinal hernias of any side and ASA score I and&#xD;
      II were included in the study. History of Immunosuppression, associated with other abdominal&#xD;
      hernias and recurrent hernia were excluded. 167 patients were in Group A or laparoscopic&#xD;
      trans abdominal preperitoneal repair group while 167 patients were in Group B or open mesh&#xD;
      repair. Data regarding length of hospital stay from both groups was recorded by researcher&#xD;
      himself on especially designed proforma.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
